## Key Takeaways

1. Strategic Purpose
Instead of using random prompts, build a structured library to measure and improve brand visibility in AI-driven search. This reveals where your brand ranks, which competitors are prioritized, and where content gaps exist.

2. Building the Framework
Create a representative sample by segmenting prompts by customer journey, product lines, and geography. Use real user language—pulled from sales calls and search data—rather than internal assumptions to ensure the prompts reflect genuine buyer behavior.

3. Actionable Implementation
Start with a "Minimum Viable Library" of 30–50 commercially critical prompts. Tag these with metadata, run them consistently across platforms, and treat the library as a living tool that evolves as your business and market trends change.

